Rating: 4
SO YUMMY! I made these last night EXACTLY as the recipe read and they are DELICIOUS! As one reader said; sweet but addictive. What more do you want in a bar cookie anyway? If you want health food snack, look elsewhere for gosh sakes! To prevent too crumbly a dough, follow directions exactly! Let a dough form while still in the food processor. It will suddenly thicken up and start to be a dough rolling around. I added BAKER'S coconut (toasted 4 min. BTW) and oatmeal right in the processor and mixed it in with short pulses. Press FIRMLY in the pan and reserve 3/4 cup, firmly packed for the topping. I used Knott's Berry Farm Jam 10 oz. jar, warmed and stirred. I am always amazed as why people wonder why the recipe didn't come out right... Try following the directions! Don't experiment the first time!

