Made these after work last night. Easy and delicious. Perhaps even better today with my morning coffee! The other reviewers who mentioned 4 minutes as being enough for toasting the coconut are absolutely right. You have to watch it like a hawk. I used unsweetened coconut from the Baker's Catalog as it was all I had. Next time, I may use sweetened coconut for the part you toast. Its moister and plumper and I think it may help the bars hold together better. Cutting them into clean slices did take a little care. I didn't reduce the sugar and didn't feel that they were too sweet. I used Dickinson's seedless Red Raspberry preserves, which spread perfectly (without heating) after a vigorous stir. If you have trouble patting the dough into the pan, cover your hand with a piece of cling-film and 'pat' through that. Can't wait to make these again for our beach picnics. A nice change of pace from the good old brownie.

